cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a novel method for image recognition, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV). The method is based on a mathematical model and involves iterative computation, which suggests that it may also fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions maximizing the ratio of between-class and within-class reconstruction error, which is a common approach in information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the experimental results involve typical databases, indicating that the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
